casebody.data:
HENRY C. DART, Plaintiff and Respondent, v. WRIGHT GILLIES, and Others, Defendants and Appellants. Ho point of interest involved in this case.

*597Before Sedgwick and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided April 7, 1879. James M. Fiske, attorney, for respondent. Wingate & Cullen, attorneys, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Judgment reversed, unless plaintiff deduct $67.75 from the verdict, and in case of such deduction, the judgment is affirmed, without costs of appeal to either party.
